entry.title: NG-14 Cygnus Release & Reentry
entry.content: The Northrop Grumman NG-14 Cygnus will be unberthed from the ISS before initiating a destructive reentry into the Earth's atmosphere taking waste along with it.

entry.title: Chang'e 5 Sample Returns to Earth
entry.content: The Chang'e 5 sample-return capsule will enter the Earth's atmosphere and land in Dorbod Banner, Inner Mongolia.

entry.title: CRS-21 Dragon Docking
entry.content: Following its launch atop a Falcon 9, the CRS-21 Dragon will autonomously dock to the ISS, bringing crew supplies as well as experiments.

entry.title: Hayabusa-2 Sample Returns to Earth
entry.content: When Hayabusa-2 flies past Earth in December 2020, it will release the capsule spinning at one revolution per three seconds. The capsule will re-enter the Earth's atmosphere at 12 km/s and it will deploy a radar-reflective parachute at an altitude of about 10 km, and eject its heat-shield, while transmitting a position beacon signal. The sample capsule will land at the Woomera Test Range in Australia.

entry.title: CRS-21 Pre-Launch News Conference
entry.content: Representatives from NASA’s International Space Station Program, SpaceX, and the U.S. Air Force’s 45th Space Wing will host a Prelaunch news conference detailing information about the CRS-21 Mission.

entry.title: Chang'e 5 Lunar Landing
entry.content:
The Chinese Chang'e 5 spacecraft is scheduled to land in the Mons Rümker region of Oceanus Procellarum, located in the northwest region of the near side of the Moon. The lander will collect 2 kg of samples which will then be placed in an ascent vehicle and brought back to Earth.
Landing time is approximate and not accurately known.

entry.title: Starship SN8 Static Fire
entry.content: SN8 will perform a static fire of its Raptor engines.
